The paper deals with the design and analysis of network coding schemes, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The focus on optimizing reception overhead suggests that the paper may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS). Finally, the use of density evolution equations for asymptotic analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
